The data
An Onfido check typically produces three main reports:
•	Document Report : Verifies the authenticity and validity of an identity document (e.g., passport, ID card, driver’s licence). It checks elements such as document format, expiry date, data consistency, and potential signs of tampering or fraud.
•	Facial Similarity Report: Confirms that the person presenting the identity document is the same person in the selfie or video capture. It performs face comparison and liveness/spoofing checks to detect impersonation or presentation attacks.
•	Device Intelligence Report: Analyses the device and network environment used during onboarding to identify potential fraud risks. It detects signals such as emulator usage, rooted devices, VPN/proxy usage, and other indicators of suspicious device behaviour.

Report Properties
a report typically contains two main components:
•	Report properties contain data extracted or generated during the verification process. These are attributes related to the applicant or the document itself, such as document type, issuing country, date of birth, or expiry date. They provide structured information extracted from the document or verification process, but do not explain whether individual checks passed or failed. 
•	Report breakdown provides the detailed results of the individual verification checks performed within a report. Each breakdown represents a specific control (e.g., image integrity, data validation, document authenticity), and shows the outcome of those checks using results such as clear, consider, failed, or unidentified.


